Start the playable/filmable chain here: [[SU 01 Surface House]]

:: Engine Contract [index] {"position":"220,0","size":"180,120"}
# Engine Contract

The engine consumes a selected `state_unit`, not the whole document.

Each state unit carries:

* LEGOS atom references.
* A PAST state.
* A PRESENT action.
* A FUTURE consequence.
* An ABC CINEOSIS seed.
* A BEFLIX recipe (one plate + a verb score).

The engine then expands that selected unit into one of two render targets:

TARGET A — CINEOSIS (generative):
* premise, temporal engine, ABC model
* 21-image matrix
* shot sequence, sound map, edit map

TARGET B — BEFLIX-128 (procedural):
* one plate + motion verbs
* a flat command list (CLR/PNT/LIN/REC/SHF)
* dot-frames generated at runtime

Both read the same unit. See [[BEFLIX Render Targets]].

[[Start]]

:: BEFLIX Render Targets [index beflix] {"position":"440,0","size":"180,120"}
# BEFLIX Render Targets

A state unit is render-target-agnostic. Its PAST / PRESENT / FUTURE is the source; the engine expands a *selected* unit — never the whole document, never stored frames.

<div class="render-a">TARGET A — CINEOSIS matrix: up to 21 image prompts (7 image-types × PAST / PRESENT / FUTURE) for a diffusion or image model. Generative.</div>

<div class="render-b">TARGET B — BEFLIX-128 program: a flat command list emitted by procedures, then executed to dot-frames. Procedural. One unit becomes one plate plus a few motion verbs, which generate many frames at zero per-frame cost.</div>

The PRESENT / FUTURE mapping is identical for either target:

<pre class="legos-data">PAST     -> establish        (held plate state, residue)
PRESENT  -> action verbs     (the shift, made motion)
FUTURE   -> consequence verbs + final hold</pre>

BEFLIX does not store images. It stores ~12 primitives, one plate per scene, and ~12 verbs. See [[BEFLIX Library]] for the registry and [[BEFLIX Recipes]] for the per-unit scores.

[[Start]] · [[Engine Contract]]

:: BEFLIX Library [data beflix] {"position":"1260,700","size":"480,340"}
# BEFLIX Library

The procedural alphabet. The Twee stores *names, signatures, and status*; the runnable implementation is the companion single file `cineosis-zork-beflix.html`. A runtime loads that engine and reads the recipes below.

<pre class="legos-data" data-kind="beflix-registry">render_targets: [cineosis_matrix, beflix_program]
companion_runtime: cineosis-zork-beflix.html
grid: 128x96   intensity: 0..7   frame_cap: 600

PLATES (9)                          status
  surface                           planned
  passage    (light / clock)        implemented
  descent    (combat)               implemented
  maze                              planned
  lair       (cyclops / thief)      planned
  temple                            planned
  dam                               planned
  river                             planned
  mine                              planned

PRIMITIVES (the marks)              status
  bgCave(b,dark)                    implemented
  mPool(b,cx,cy,r)                  implemented
  figure(b,x,y,pose,v)             implemented
  bar(b,gap,y)                      implemented
  swordGlow(b,x,y,v)               implemented
  floorBand(b,y)                    implemented
  grueEyes(b,cx,cy)                implemented
  water_line(b,y)                   planned
  bell_rings(b,cx,cy,n)            planned
  eye_disc(b,x,y,open)             planned
  flame(b,x,y)                      planned
  glint(b,x,y)                      planned
  dot_haze(b,x,y,w,h,d)           planned
  rainbow_bands(b,solid)           planned

VERBS (transforms = REC loops)      status
  establish slam ignite strike      implemented
  travel drainbattery               implemented
  drain rise exorcise double        planned
  dig thicken compress dissolve     planned
  openEye speakName deposit win     planned

PHASES
  emit      primitives push commands; they draw, never REC
  interpret a VM runs the flat list; REC snapshots the grid
  render    each cell -> a dot sized by intensity</pre>

