:: Validator Checklist [validator] {"position":"360,700","size":"340,320"}
# Validator Checklist

Before this drives an engine:

1. Every id is unique.
2. Every referenced id exists.
3. Every treasure has a lifecycle path ending in `deposited`.
4. Every obstacle has at least one resolving shift.
5. Every shift has preconditions and postconditions.
6. Every state unit has `past`, `present`, and `future`.
7. Every state unit names concrete visible material for ABC CINEOSIS.
8. Map edges are explicit; generic maze / river summaries are not enough for runtime navigation.
9. Duplicate aliases are resolved.
10. Missing atoms are added: `loc_loud`, `loc_stone_barrow`, exact maze cells, exact river cells.

BEFLIX render-target checks:

11. Every state unit has a BEFLIX recipe: one plate, plus verbs for PRESENT and FUTURE.
12. Every recipe references only plates, primitives, and verbs declared in [[BEFLIX Library]].
13. No recipe hardcodes coordinates; motion comes from shared primitives plus verbs.
14. Implemented plates render within `frame_cap`; planned plates are marked, not assumed.
15. The same unit must expand to either render target — CINEOSIS matrix or BEFLIX program — from one source.

